Let's start by computing the first few terms of the sequence to identify any patterns:
1. \(v_1 = b\)
2. \(v_2 = \frac{2}{v_1 - 1} = \frac{2}{b - 1}\)
3. \(v_3 = \frac{2}{v_2 - 1} = \frac{2}{\frac{2}{b - 1} - 1} = \frac{2}{\frac{2 - (b - 1)}{b - 1}} = \frac{2(b - 1)}{2 - (b - 1)} = \frac{2(b - 1)}{3 - b}\)
4. \(v_4 = \frac{2}{v_3 - 1} = \frac{2}{\frac{2(b - 1)}{3 - b} - 1} = \frac{2}{\frac{2(b - 1) - (3 - b)}{3 - b}} = \frac{2(3 - b)}{2(b - 1) - (3 - b)} = \frac{2(3 - b)}{2b - 2 - 3 + b} = \frac{2(3 - b)}{3b - 5}\)

