3. She will then install a new game that requires 15 gigabytes. So, the new space occupied after installing the game will be \(37 + 15 = 52\) gigabytes.
4. After these operations, the remaining free space on her current laptop will be \(80 - 52 = 28\) gigabytes. This will include the space taken up by the files she wants to transfer.
5. She plans to transfer these files to a new laptop with a 120-gigabyte hard drive. After transferring the 28 gigabytes of files, the remaining free space on the new laptop will be \(120 - 28 = 92\) gigabytes.

