1. The number is of the form $p_1^3$ (i.e., $n = p_1 \times p_1 \times p_1$).
2. The number is of the form $p_1 \times p_2$ (i.e., $n = p_1 \times p_2$).

The smallest number in the first form is $2^3 = 8$, and the smallest number in the second form is $2 \times 3 = 6$. Since 6 is smaller than 8, the smallest positive integer with exactly four positive divisors is 6.

