Thus, we have 15 possible combinations. We need to choose 3 out of these 15 combinations such that no two combinations are the same. The number of ways to choose 3 combinations out of 15 is given by the combination formula \(\binom{15}{3}\):
\[
\binom{15}{3} = \frac{15!}{3!(15-3)!} = \frac{15 \times 14 \times 13}{3 \times 2 \times 1} = 455
\]
Therefore, the number of ways to distribute the fruits among the baskets is \(\boxed{455}\).
