I0320 15:51:05.533422 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Mr. Maxwell takes 1 hr to drive to work in the morning but 1 and half hours to drive back home in the evening. If the morning and evening traffic is similar and he drives at an average speed of 30mph in the morning, what is the average speed of his return journey?
I0320 15:51:05.533525 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine the average speed of Mr. Maxwell's return journey, we first need to calculate the distance he travels to work in the morning. Given that he drives at an average speed of 30 mph for 1 hour, the distance can be calculated as follows:

\[
\text{Distance to work} = \text{Speed} \times \text{Time} = 30 \, \text{mph} \times 1 \, \text{hour} = 30 \, \text{miles}
\]

Since the distance to work is the same as the distance back home, the distance for the return journey is also 30 miles. The time taken for the return journey is given as 1.5 hours. The average speed for the return journey can be calculated using the formula:

\[
\text{Average speed} = \frac{\text{Distance}}{\text{Time}} = \frac{30 \, \text{miles}}{1.5 \, \text{hours}} = 20 \, \text{mph}
\]

Thus, the average speed of his return journey is:

\[
\boxed{20}
\]
