1. Initially, the total cost of the boat is $2400, and it is shared equally among 8 students. After the bake sale, the remaining cost after deducting the $800 earned is $2400 - $800 = $1600.
2. Since the remaining cost is $1600 and now only 6 students will share this cost (because Alex and Ben dropped out), each of the remaining students now has to pay $\frac{1600}{6}$.

We will calculate the amount each of the remaining students has to pay using Python.
```python
# Initial total cost of the boat
