Before the bake sale, each student had to pay $\frac{2400}{8} = 300$. Now they have to pay $266.67. So, each of the remaining students has to pay $300 - 266.67 = 33.33$ less.

However, since the question asks for how much more each of the remaining students has to pay now that Alex and Ben aren't participating, we can conclude that each of the remaining students has to pay an additional $33.33 more to account for the reduction in the number of students sharing the cost.

Therefore, the answer is \(\boxed{33.33}\).
