I0320 16:18:40.995168 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Mark made a chalkboard that is 3 feet wide. It is 2 times as long as it is wide. What is the area of the chalkboard?
I0320 16:18:40.995262 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine the area of the chalkboard, we start by identifying the dimensions given in the problem. The width of the chalkboard is 3 feet, and the length is 2 times the width. Therefore, we can calculate the length as follows:

\[
\text{Length} = 2 \times \text{Width} = 2 \times 3 = 6 \text{ feet}
\]

Next, we use the formula for the area of a rectangle, which is given by the product of its length and width:

\[
\text{Area} = \text{Length} \times \text{Width} = 6 \times 3 = 18 \text{ square feet}
\]

Thus, the area of the chalkboard is \(\boxed{18}\).
