Then, we calculate the number of gold stones:
\[ 3 \text{ rows} \times 10 \text{ stones per row} = 30 \text{ gold stones} \]

Now, we sum the number of stones from all three types:
\[ 36 \text{ pink stones} + 56 \text{ silver stones} + 30 \text{ gold stones} = 122 \text{ stones} \]

Therefore, the total number of stones Emily adds is:
\[ \boxed{122} \]
