I0320 16:26:31.758424 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 Let's define the number of seashells Emma has as \( E \). According to the problem, Sophia has one-third as many seashells as Emma, so the number of seashells Sophia has is \( \frac{E}{3} \). Mia has 3 more than three times the number of seashells that Sophia has, so the number of seashells Mia has is \( 3 \left( \frac{E}{3} \right) + 3 = E + 3 \).

