I0320 16:53:21.206181 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Mia has a novel with 472 pages. She has already read 187 pages. If she reads 25 pages a day for 6 days, how many pages does she still have left to read?
I0320 16:53:21.206315 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine how many pages Mia still has left to read, we need to follow these steps:

1. Calculate the total number of pages Mia will read in 6 days.
2. Subtract the pages she has already read and the pages she will read in the next 6 days from the total number of pages in the novel.

Step 1: Calculate the total number of pages Mia will read in 6 days.
\[
25 \text{ pages/day} \times 6 \text{ days} = 150 \text{ pages}
\]

Step 2: Add the pages she has already read to the pages she will read in the next 6 days to find out the total number of pages she will have read by the end of her reading.
\[
187 \text{ pages} + 150 \text{ pages} = 337 \text{ pages}
\]

Step 3: Subtract the total number of pages she will have read by the end of her reading from the total number of pages in the novel.
\[
472 \text{ pages} - 337 \text{ pages} = 135 \text{ pages}
\]

Therefore, the number of pages Mia still has left to read is \(\boxed{135}\).
