To determine the value of the savings account after five years with a decreasing annual interest rate, we need to calculate the effect of each year's interest rate on the account balance. The initial deposit is \$1000, and the interest rate starts at 10% and decreases by 1% each subsequent year. The interest rates for each year are 10%, 9%, 8%, 7%, and 6%.

The value of the account at the end of each year can be calculated by multiplying the previous year's balance by \(1 + \text{interest rate}\).

