I0320 17:04:12.795117 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Mario needs to transport 720 pounds of apples that are packed into 40-pound boxes. If the shipping cost of each box is $2.2, how much will Mario pay for the transportation?
I0320 17:04:12.795188 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine the total cost for transporting the apples, we need to follow these steps:

1. Calculate the number of 40-pound boxes needed to transport 720 pounds of apples.
2. Determine the total shipping cost by multiplying the number of boxes by the cost per box.

Step 1: Calculate the number of 40-pound boxes needed.
\[ \text{Number of boxes} = \frac{\text{Total weight of apples}}{\text{Weight per box}} = \frac{720 \text{ pounds}}{40 \text{ pounds/box}} \]
\[ \text{Number of boxes} = 18 \text{ boxes} \]

Step 2: Determine the total shipping cost.
\[ \text{Total shipping cost} = \text{Number of boxes} \times \text{Cost per box} = 18 \times 2.2 \]
\[ \text{Total shipping cost} = 39.6 \]

So, Mario will pay \(\boxed{39.6}\) dollars for the transportation.
