I0320 17:28:37.314960 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Problem:
An isosceles triangle $ABC$ has two sides of length 8 cm and a base of length 6 cm. A rectangle has one side on the base of triangle $ABC$ and a vertex on each of the two congruent sides of triangle $ABC$. What is the length of one side of the rectangle, in cm? Express your answer as a common fraction.

[asy]
defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
size(4cm,4cm);

pair A,B,C;

A=(0,0);
