I0320 17:43:11.889019 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine the total weight of 7 white rhinos and 8 black rhinos, we need to start by converting the weight of the black rhino from tons to pounds. Since 1 ton is equal to 2000 pounds, each black rhino weighs 2000 pounds.

Next, we calculate the total weight of the white rhinos. If one white rhino weighs 5100 pounds, then 7 white rhinos will weigh:
\[ 7 \times 5100 = 35700 \text{ pounds} \]

Now, we calculate the total weight of the black rhinos. If one black rhino weighs 2000 pounds, then 8 black rhinos will weigh:
\[ 8 \times 2000 = 16000 \text{ pounds} \]

To find the total weight of all the rhinos, we add the weight of the white rhinos and the black rhinos together:
\[ 35700 + 16000 = 51700 \text{ pounds} \]

Thus, the total weight of 7 white rhinos and 8 black rhinos is:
\[ \boxed{51700} \]
