I0320 17:46:21.698810 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] prompts:	Lily wants to tile her living room that measures 18 feet by 12 feet. There is a fireplace area that measures 2 feet by 4 feet which will not be tiled. How many square feet of tile will Lily need for her living room?
I0320 17:46:21.699029 127102378575424 reward_manager.py:164] completions:	 To determine how many square feet of tile Lily will need for her living room, we start by calculating the total area of the living room and then subtract the area of the fireplace.

1. Calculate the area of the living room:
   The area of a rectangle is given by the formula:
   \[
   \text{Area} = \text{length} \times \text{width}
   \]
   For the living room, this calculation is:
   \[
   \text{Area of the living room} = 18 \, \text{feet} \times 12 \, \text{feet} = 216 \, \text{square feet}
   \]

2. Calculate the area of the fireplace:
   The area of the fireplace is given by:
   \[
   \text{Area of the fireplace} = 2 \, \text{feet} \times 4 \, \text{feet} = 8 \, \text{square feet}
   \]

3. Subtract the area of the fireplace from the area of the living room to find the area that will be tiled:
   \[
   \text{Area to be tiled} = 216 \, \text{square feet} - 8 \, \text{square feet} = 208 \, \text{square feet}
   \]

Therefore, Lily will need \(\boxed{208}\) square feet of tile for her living room.
