     \[
     12,015 = 3^6 \times 5 \times 29
     \]

   - For \(10,080\):
     \[
     10,080 = 2^4 \times 3^2 \times 5 \times 7
     \]

3. **The LCM is the product of the highest power of each prime factor present in the factorization of either number**:
   \[
   \text{LCM}(12,015, 10,080) = 2^4 \times 3^6 \times 5^1 \times 29 \times 7^1
   \]

