This holds for all \( x \), indicating that the graphs are identical and will intersect at every point, not just two. However, the problem implies that we are looking for the value where the graphs intersect at the minimum of two points. Since the graphs are identical, they intersect at every point, and the simplest form of such problem would imply \( n = 0 \) as the value.

