2. **Calculate the arctangent of \( \frac{1}{2w_k} \):**
   For each root \( w_k \), the tangent value \( \tan \left( \arctan \left( \frac{1}{2w_k} \right) \right) \) is \( \frac{1}{2w_k} \). So, we need to sum \( \frac{1}{2w_k} \) over all roots, and then compute the tangent of this sum.

3. **Sum the arctangents and compute the tangent:**
   The sum of the arctangents is \( \sum_{k=1}^n \arctan \left( \frac{1}{2w_k} \right) \), and the tangent of this sum is \( \tan \left( \sum_{k=1}^n \arctan \left( \frac{1}{2w_k} \right) \right) \).

