   \[
   j(b) = \frac{2b + 1}{b - 1}
   \]

2. Then, we need to find the value of \( h(j(b)) \) in terms of \( b \). This means substituting \( j(b) \) into \( h(x) \):

   \[
   h(j(b)) = \left( \frac{2b + 1}{b - 1} \right)^3 - 1 = 27
