\[ A = \begin{pmatrix} 0 & -1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & -1 \\ 1 & 0 & 0 \end{pmatrix} \]

To find $A$, we can begin by computing the cross product of the vectors $\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}$. Then, we can use the cross product to form the matrix $A$.

The cross product of the vectors \(\begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ -1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$ and \(\begin{pmatrix} 2 \\ 0 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix}\) is:

\[ \begin{pmatrix}
(2 \times (-1) - 0 \times 7) \\
(3 \times (-1) - 0 \times 5) \\
0 \times (5 - (-1))
\end{pmatrix}
\]

These computations lead to the vector:
\[ \begin{pmatrix}
0 \\ -5 \\ -1
\end{pmatrix}

The matrix $A$ can be derived in the form \(\begin{pmatrix} 0 & -1 & 0 \\ 0 & 0 & -1 \\ 1 & 0 & 0 \end{pmatrix}\). Therefore, we can verify these values using the given equations:
